parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension and steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to steer, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
wanders
or drifts while driving
the front end bounces excessively
the vehicle is difficult to steer
the front shock bracket breaks due to weld failure
front end alignment failure causing damage to tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic leveling jack can cause the vehicle to fall off the jack during the leveling process, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The leveling jack extends and the vehicle falls off during the leveling process
the jack does not work properly under most parking conditions
the jack fails to level and stabilize the vehicle when parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic jack system can cause the vehicle to fall off the jack during the leveling process, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The hydraulic jacks fail
the leveling jack does not work properly
the vehicle is unable to be leveled and stabilized when parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling fan can cause the engine to overheat, leading to premature wear, damage, or even engine failure, which can result in costly repairs, reduced vehicle performance, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The cooling fan does not turn on
the cooling fan is noisy
the temperature gauge is in the red zone
the engine overheats
the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine main seal can cause engine oil to leak, leading to premature wear, damage, or even engine failure, which can result in costly repairs, reduced vehicle performance, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaks from the engine
oil spots under the vehicle
the engine oil level is low
the engine makes unusual noises
the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the propane and CO sensors can cause the vehicle's safety features to malfunction, potentially leading to carbon monoxide poisoning or other hazardous situations.
symptoms: The propane and CO sensor warning lights are illuminated
the vehicle's ventilation system does not function properly
the vehicle's safety features do not activate in response to hazardous conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent generator failure can cause the battery to drain, leading to unexpected stalls, loss of power, and reduced vehicle performance, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The generator/light alternator warning light comes on
the battery drains quickly
the vehicle stalls or has difficulty starting
the electrical accessories malfunction or fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery failure can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to unexpected breakdowns and reduced vehicle performance, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle has difficulty starting
the battery drains quickly
the electrical accessories malfunction or fail
the vehicle stalls or has reduced power.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Wiring Causing Tag Axle Brake Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty wiring can cause the tag axle brakes to fail, leading to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake warning light comes on
the brakes feel spongy or soft
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes make unusual noises or vibrations.
